Lipid cyst: classic and atypical appearances.
 Lipid cysts, a specific type of fat necrosis, frequently have a pathognomonic appearance on radiographs.
 This consists of a lucent lesion surrounded by a smooth rim that may or not be calcified.
 Occasionally, lipid cysts with unusual mammographic appearances are encountered.
 An appreciation of some of these appearances may prevent unnecessary biopsies.
